Wema Bank Plc at the weekend ended its third SME Business School in Abuja. In partnership with Abuja Enterprise Agency, The SME Business School began on March 14, this year. The platform was aimed at equipping owners with  skills that will enable them to run their businesses more profitably.   Union Bank touches lives on Employees Volunteer Day     Interswitch seeks biometric adoption to tackle e-fraud     Russia-Ukraine: Nigerian banks not under any major risk,…   According to a statement by the bank, 150 participants graduated  from the programme where facilitators from Swifta, IBFC Alliance, Pedabo Consulting Limited, MTN, Development Bank of Nigeria, Reap and Arcenciel, Africa 118, and Soule Melange featured. The bank said the idea of the business school came after its research and   studies by global business organisations, that there were areas small and medium enterprises owners were grappling with. Through the Business School, the bank has been supporting SMEs by bridging these gaps and equipping them to respond to challenges in the business environment. Wema Bank held the the maiden edition last year at Sheraton Hotel, Ikeja Lagos with participants  trained in finance, marketing and sales, leadership, customer service, technology, branding, strategy, innovation and business transformation.